nib.text:
A man was injured in a shooting in north Minneapolis Tuesday afternoon, police said.

MPD officers responded to a report of shots fired on the 3500 block of Emerson Avenue North around 4:25 p.m.

When they arrived, officers found a man with a gunshot wound.

The man was taken to an area hospital for treatment of his injury which was considered not life-threatening.

The circumstances surrounding the shooting remain under investigation.
